'''Juan Manuel Sanabria Magole''' (born 29 March 2000) is a Uruguayan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] or [[left-back]] for [[Major League Soccer]] club [[Real Salt Lake]]<ref>{{Cite web |last=rsl |title=Real Salt Lake Acquires 25-Year-Old Uruguayan Juan Manuel Sanabria From Liga MX Club Atlético San Luis {{!}} Real Salt Lake |url=https://www.rsl.com/news/real-salt-lake-acquires-25-year-old-uruguayan-juan-manuel-sanabria-from-liga-mx-club-atletico-san-luis |access-date=2026-02-10 |website=rsl |language=en}}</ref> and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|474141}}</ref>

==Club career==
Sanabria was born in [[Florida, Uruguay|Florida]], and joined [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional]]'s youth setup in 2012 from hometown side Club Nacional de Florida. In January 2017, [[Atlético Madrid]] reached an agreement with Nacional for the transfer of Sanabria, with the player joining his new club after his 18th birthday.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elobservador.com.uy/nota/juan-manuel-sanabria-otro-uruguayo-en-atletico-madrid--2019819300|title=Juan Manuel Sanabria, otro uruguayo en Atlético Madrid|trans-title=Juan Manuel Sanabria, another Uruguayan in Atlético Madrid|publisher=[[El Observador (Uruguay)|El Observador]]|language=es|date=4 August 2019|accessdate=26 January 2021}}</ref> He officially joined ''Atleti'' on 23 July 2018, being assigned to the ''Juvenil A'' squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/juan-manuel-sanabria-nuevo-futbolista-del-atletico-de-madrid-juvenil-a|title=Juan Manuel Sanabria, nuevo futbolista del Atlético de Madrid Juvenil A|trans-title=Juan Manuel Sanabria, new footballer of Atlético de Madrid ''Juvenil A''|publisher=Atlético Madrid|language=es|date=23 July 2018|accessdate=26 January 2021}}</ref>

Promoted to [[Atlético Madrid B|the reserves]] for the [[2019–20 Segunda División B|2019–20 campaign]], Sanabria made his senior debut on 24 August 2019, starting in a 2–1 [[Segunda División B]] away win against [[Marino de Luanco]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/remontada-rojiblanca-en-luanco|title=Remontada rojiblanca en Luanco|trans-title=Red-and-white comeback in Luanco|publisher=Atlético Madrid|language=es|date=24 August 2019|accessdate=26 January 2021}}</ref> His first senior goal came on 7 September, as he scored the winner in a 2–1 success at [[UP Langreo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/atletico-madrid/20190907/47223467587/el-atleti-b-se-llevo-el-triunfo-de-langreo-tras-un-final-de-locos.html|title=El Atleti B se llevó el triunfo de Langreo tras un final de locos|trans-title=''Atleti'' B got the win from Langreo in a crazy ending|publisher=[[Mundo Deportivo]]|language=es|date=8 September 2019|accessdate=26 January 2021}}</ref>

Sanabria made his first team debut for ''Atleti'' on 16 December 2020, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Ángel Correa]] in a 3–0 away win against [[CD Cardassar]], for [[2020–21 Copa del Rey|the season]]'s [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/2020/12/16/copa_del_rey/1608148286_528240.html|title=El Atleti se divierte ante un Cardassar que estuvo a la altura|trans-title=''Atleti'' have some fun against a Cardassar who was up to it|publisher=[[Diario AS]]|language=es|date=16 December 2020|accessdate=26 January 2021}}</ref> The following 26 January, he was loaned to [[Segunda División]] side [[Real Zaragoza]] for the remainder of [[2020–21 Segunda División|the campaign]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/acuerdo-con-el-real-zaragoza-para-la-cesion-de-juan-manuel-sanabria|title=Acuerdo con el Real Zaragoza para la cesión de Juan Manuel Sanabria|trans-title=Agreement with Real Zaragoza for the loan of Juan Manuel Sanabria|publisher=Atlético Madrid|language=es|date=26 January 2021|accessdate=26 January 2021}}</ref>

Sanabria made his professional debut on 12 February 2021, replacing [[Sergio Bermejo]] in a 1–1 away draw against [[CE Sabadell FC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/segunda-division/sabadell-vs-zaragoza/cronica/2021/02/12/6026dacc46163f7f598b457c.html|title=El acierto o no desde el punto de penalti decide el empate|trans-title=The aim or the lack of from the penalty spot decide the draw|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|language=es|date=12 February 2021|accessdate=13 February 2021}}</ref>

On 10 February 2026, Sanabria joined [[Major League Soccer]] side [[Real Salt Lake]] until the end of their 2029-30 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rsl.com/news/real-salt-lake-acquires-25-year-old-uruguayan-juan-manuel-sanabria-from-liga-mx-club-atletico-san-luis|title=Real Salt Lake Acquires 25-Year-Old Uruguayan Juan Manuel Sanabria From Liga MX Club Atlético San Luis &#124; Real Salt Lake|website=rsl}}</ref>

==International career==
Sanabria has represented Uruguay at various youth levels.<ref>{{cite web|title=18 – Juan Manuel Sanabria|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/18-juan-manuel-sanabria499547/|access-date=13 February 2021}}</ref> With 88 caps for youth national teams, he has represented Uruguay at the [[2015 South American U-15 Championship]], [[2017 South American U-17 Championship]], [[2019 South American U-20 Championship]], [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] and the [[2020 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Datos del plantel Sub-23|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/datos-del-plantel-sub-23/|access-date=13 February 2021}}</ref>

In June 2025, Sanabria received his first call-up to the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Uruguay dio a conocer los 29 convocados para Eliminatorias: sorpresas, vueltas y ausencias|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-los-29-convocados-para-Eliminatorias-sorpresas-vueltas-y-ausencias-uc925821|language=es|date=3 June 2025|access-date=3 June 2025}}</ref> He made his debut on 10 October 2025 in a 1–0 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] win against the [[Dominican Republic national football team|Dominican Republic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Seleccion--Que-dijeron-los-jugadores-tras-el-1-0-ante-Dominicana-y-quienes-debutaron--uc939429|title=Selección: ¿Qué dijeron los jugadores tras el 1-0 ante Dominicana y quiénes debutaron?|language=es|date=10 October 2025|accessdate=10 October 2025}}</ref> He scored his first goal three days later, on 13 October, in a 2–1 win over [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/mundial/nota/_/id/15808524/juan-manuel-sanabria-hizo-su-primer-gol-con-seleccion-uruguaya-vs-uzbekistan|title=Juan Manuel Sanabria hizo su primer gol con la Selección Uruguaya ante Uzbekistán|language=es|date=13 October 2025|accessdate=14 October 2025}}</ref> On 31 May 2026, he was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Sanabria is the elder brother of footballer [[Lucas Sanabria (Uruguayan footballer)|Lucas Sanabria]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elpais.com.uy/ovacion/futbol/lucas-sanabria-viaja-a-diario-desde-florida-recoba-lo-probo-en-otro-puesto-y-en-europa-ya-preguntan-por-el|title=Lucas Sanabria: viaja a diario desde Florida, Recoba lo probó en otro puesto y en Europa ya preguntan por él|date=24 February 2024|access-date=1 September 2024}}</ref>

